		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p150715">Re: Windows IME is stupid!</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=150715&amp;sid=068e6ba2c08e48c13ce2f0dbaa7611d0#p150715"><img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/styles/tjp-embed/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=91970&amp;sid=068e6ba2c08e48c13ce2f0dbaa7611d0">kurisuto</a></strong> &raquo; Sat 04.11.2009 11:47 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">And btw I think that's a great feature of the Japanese language : by adding furiganas that don't match the actual kanjis used, you can add subtle nuances (or not so subtle for that matter) and sometimes it even works as a &quot;real-time footnote&quot;, whereas in &quot;our&quot; languages you would have to put it into parentheses, use an apposition or an actual footnote, which could break the rythm of the sentence (or lead to other stylistic problems). Just one of the many reasons why I love Japanese...</div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile150715">
